        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.14914/2604.14914v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Geometry vs. Language Diversity. (Left) Text-conditioned generation exhibits a “sink trap’ effect, where diverse prompts for a “rabbit” yield nearly identical geometries. (Right) In contrast, our unconditioned 3D generative model overcomes this linguistic bottleneck, faithfully inverting and reconstructing arbitrary 3D shapes with high fidelity.",
                "position": 286
            }
        ]
